 Dhaka, Sep 3 (bdnews24.com)Bourses finished down on Wednesday as investor sell-offs continued from the previous day, leading nearly 70 percent of the traded issues to fall. Dhaka Stock Exchange's benchmark DGEN or general index fell 34.09 points, or 1.20 percent, to end on 2797.31. The DSI or all-share price index finished 25.64 points, or 0.63 percent, down at 2390.67. The blue-chip DSE-20 fell 15.47 points, or 0.63 percent, to close at 2418.75. All indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange also closed down as mutual funds, banks and insurers witnessed huge losses. The CSCX or selective categories index was down 55.60 points, or 0.97 percent, to close on 5646.95. The CASPI or all-share price index closed at 8654.43, slumping 76.66 points or 0.87 percent. The bourse's blue-chip CSE-30 ended down 56.33 points, or 0.71 percent, on 7788.46. Turnover on the DSE was Tk 2.69 billionwith 16,925,983 shares changing handsdown from Tk 2.71 billion the previous day. Turnover on the port city bourse crept up to Tk 366.80 million from Tuesday's Tk 308.66 million, with 3,376,103 traded shares. Losers outnumbered gainers on the DSE by 171 to 44, while 14 issues held steady. On the CSE, 102 issues lost, 27 gained, and five remained unchanged. Titas Gas topped the turnover board, closing at Tk 420.25, down by 1.81 percent. Beximco was second in line, surging 12.52 percent from the previous day, to finish at Tk 121.30. Grameen One: Scheme 2 lost 3.02 percent to end on Tk 41.70 after investors locked in profit. ACI ended on Tk 516.40, edging down 0.71 percent while Beximco Pharmaceuticals advanced 1.08 percent to Tk 111.70. Among the other scrips on the turnover board, Lanka Bangla Finance, ICB AMCL 2nd NRB Mutual Fund, Square Pharmaceuticals and Uttara Bank lost on profit taking. Pragati Insurance gained. b
